sync_partners.general: If an key is missing, that means no, not, off, 0, like if disabled is missing, that means not disabled
sync_partners.source: https://wiki.mediamath.com/display/mmEngineering/RTB+Exchange+ID+List which is missing a lot of information
sync_partners.sorting: Sorry this is unsorted but whenever I run it through a JSON formatter it just does its own random unsort despite my original order
sync_partners.map_storage: [MP] Who stores the mapping data MediaMath, Partner

sync_urls.https: The URL used to sync secure UUID is expanded by us into the uuid= cookie value of the browser. If missing, no secure sync is available
sync_urls.http: The URL used to sync non secure UUID is expanded by us into the uuid= cookie value of the browser
sync_urls.incoming: sync urls used by external websites and parters to hit MT2 (always being with pixel.mathtag.com or sync.mathtag.com
sync_urls.outbound: sync urls that MediaMath sends browsers to

sync_partners.disabled:: [0, 1] 1 = do not use this. Do not sync with this
sync_partners.segment_space: Where this data is stored in The Segment Database (SDB). What MongoDB subkey is used
sync_partners.common_name: The common name this sync partner is called
sync_partners.type: [data,exchange] either a data partner or an RTB exchange
sync_partners.placeholder: used for mass editing, not a real usable value
